<div class="article-section" id="4">
	<h1>Security</h1>

	<h2>- Is my money safe with KiyanPay?</h2>

	<p>We're signed up to the Financial Services Compensation Scheme (FSCS), which mean your money is protected up to a value of £85,000.</p>

	<h2>- What do you do with my information?</h2>

	<p>All information provided will be managed and recorded on our secure data basis. This is recorded to be compliant with the regulations set by our regulators. This information is not passed on to third party’s unless consented to by our privacy policy. You are able to deactivate your account at any time however we can’t delete your information.</p>

	<h2>- I don’t recognise a payment what do I do?</h2>

	<p>Please contact us through the contact Centre straight away so we can assist with the problem. We have a very helpful team that will assist you.</p>

	<h2>- I’ve received a suspicious email – what do I do?</h2>

	<p>Please do not click on any of the links its most likely a scam, we will never send an email asking for internet banking or personal information. Please forward the email to info@kiyanpay.com. Once sent please delete the email.</p>

	<h2>- How do I report a scam?</h2>

	<p>Sometimes scams are hard to identify and you might have been tricked by a fraudster. Please contact us through the contact Centre straight away so we can assist with the problem. We have a very helpful team that will assist you
</p>
</div>
